President Biden spoke with Sheikh Tamim Bin Hamad Al-Thani of Qatar about the importance of protecting civilians and increasing humanitarian aid to Gaza. They welcomed the $100 million commitment from the GCC and expressed gratitude for Qatar's efforts in securing the release of hostages, including two American citizens. President Biden condemned the holding of hostages by Hamas, including a 3-year old American citizen. They agreed that all hostages must be released without delay. President Biden reiterated his vision for a future Palestinian state and acknowledged that Hamas has hindered progress towards that goal. Both leaders committed to working towards a more peaceful and stable Middle East region.